name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: If you love nature and want some peace and quiet away from the city, this is the perfect place. I love how it feels like you’re in the middle of the jungle sometimes. It’s a great escape and don’t be put off by the fact it’s a reservoir, it’s probably the nicest reservoir you’ll get to visit!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
The limitless beauty that macritchie offers can only be described as breathtaking, yet tranquil. Strolling into the park, one is instantly surrounded by  greenery and immensed in its verdant nature.

A popular activity that can be enjoyed by people of all ages is hiking on the boardwalk by the river as it is a mind calming activity that truly allows one to experience the thick forest and invigorating waters of the reservoir at the same time. And, if you are lucky, you would be able to spot a stingray or even different reptiles taking a dip in the waters.

Apart from hiking on the broad and well paved trails, one can also rent canoes and kayak around the reservoir. There is also a designated area for fishing and a cafe conveniently situated near the parking lot for one to grab a bite or quench their thirst. However, do be careful of monkeys and do not bother them as they may get aggressive.

Overall, a visit to macritchie is indeed a 9.7/10 experience.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: We did a 15km trail walk along the boardwalk, through the tree top sky walk and trails. Great way to get some exercise and take in the beauty of the scenery and wildlife.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Scenic and beautiful place. It’s a 11 km stretch across the reservoir.  You will experience board walk near the water, walking through forest up and down. Some part of the walk is by the golf course. Overall a wonderful experience. You must try once.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
This a beautiful rainforest walk. We spent 4 hours walking. There are different trails. We did all of them. There are short trails that are entirely on the boardwalk. The rest are on a cleared path. The tree top walk is amazing. You cross a suspended bridge.
There are monkeys everywhere. Beware, they will grab a plastic bag if they see it. One climbed up my daughter's leg when she stopped to take a photo! . Once past the boardwalk, there are fewer monkeys to be seen. We also saw turtles, water monitors, birds, squirrels. The rainforest is a peaceful piece of paradise with beautiful birdsong. There is a Cafe at the start. You can also kayak. This is a must do if you enjoy nature walks. Make sure you have decent walking shoes. Much of the walk is in the shade. There are a couple of ranger stations on the way to refill water bottles and toilet stops. Do not carry plastic bags even in back pack. A monkey jumped on my backpack and unzipped it, taking out the contents. I tried to take the plastic from it but it bared its teeth. I picked up plastic bag remnants and juice bottles on the walk so it obviously happens often.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of Singapore’s most tranquil parks to be in. The reservoir is vase enough so even though it may seems crowded in a given day and time like the morning weekends, it doesn’t feel crowded. The trails are well lite, and the broad walk well paved. Weekends are filled with various schools running their canoeing 🛶 CCA activities. The water colour in the reservoir has a clear turquoise green glow. It is stocked with fish and there’s a section designated for fishing 🎣. The Mushroom Cafe is a stone’s throw away from the carpark. As for the residential monkey population, if you don’t bother them, they wouldn’t bother you, just be careful if you’re holding bags of food. Enjoy!😊

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Put on your hiking shoes, spend at least 2-3 hours to unwind

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Nature at its best with Human Intervention.

The place is well maintained (hence human intervention) and one can see if full of nature.

The MacRitchie Reservoir and the nearby hiking/trailing path is a bliss for adventure goers.
This is your ideal spot for weekends.

There are several concrete pathways that serve a good running track.

The park is equipped with lush greenery, water body (obviously) and monkeys. 🙈 🙉 🙊

There are boardwalks all along the perimeter of the reservoir and through the forest for walk-amid-nature.
There are few seatings in between for enjoying a moment of serendipity.

The best sunset view is from the Paddle Lodge, keep your camera ready and see the Sun go down and while its doing that enjoy the beaming reflection on the stretch of water body for soothing view.

The park is filled with families, group of friends, couple, individuals runners, etc so yes enjoy it in all elements.

We spent few hours here, and are defined coming back to cover more of those boardwalks and see where it takes us.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Well maintained and beautiful area for hiking. Plenty of scenic views for taking photographs. We were fully drenched when it rained but it was an enjoyable experience.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: It is one of my favorite nature park. Good place for hiking. Good view. You can see a lot of monkeys. Watch the sunset. I always go from Windsor nature park to MacRitchie park. Saw a AED in Jelutong Hut.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Well connected from all places within city, this place is well visited by many people regularly like me. Multiple walking trails with proper walking tracks, broadways, and some with stones and mud the natural way. If we cover the entire reservoir we end up walking 15-18 kilometers. There are multiple scenic places to capture. Treetop bridge is where everyone walks first, though it’s not very high place, but, a must visit and check. Walking trails are good for health and refreshing too.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: The trekking trails are amazing out here. You have the options to choose the difficulty levels as well. The views are amazing. You can encounter monkeys and monitor lizards here, so be aware of them. Keep yourself hydrated for the entire duration by carrying a water bottle. There is a place near the tree top bridge to refill the water bottle. Washrooms are available too.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
MacRitchie Reservoir is a beautiful and serene oasis in the heart of Singapore. The reservoir is surrounded by lush green forests and is perfect for nature lovers and outdoor enthusiasts. The highlight of the reservoir is its scenic walking trail that offers spectacular views of the water and the surrounding foliage.
The walking trail is well-maintained and clearly marked, making it easy for visitors to explore the reservoir at their own pace. There are several different routes to choose from, ranging from easy to challenging, so there's something for everyone.
One of the best things about the reservoir is the abundance of wildlife that can be spotted along the way. From monkeys swinging through the trees to exotic birds and butterflies.
Overall, MacRitchie Reservoir is a must-visit destination for anyone looking to escape the hustle and bustle of the city and get back to nature.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Spent this place for 2nd time to see the tree top trail which is close during my 1st visit. Nature lovers out there come and visit this place. I earned 22657 steps this visit (June 25 2022)

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of the greatest trail to hike in Singapore covering a distance of 11 kilometres. Away from the hustle and bustle city and enjoy the walk into the wild surrounded with flora and fauna

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Highly recommend to hike here. There’re many available routes, and the navigation is very useful. The TreeTop Walk is the highlight. There’re some monkeys around, but they do no harm to visitors.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Another favorite spot to walk & enjoy the breeze of the reservoir. Quite a vast area to cover so best to walk within one's own pace & timing 👍

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: I'm speechless when I went there. So beautiful. Really Nature reserved. Worth it. You must visit this place. I think this park is much better for mind Relaxation compare to other Singapore parks. I really do love it

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Lovely place for a morning or early evening walk or jog ! A treasure trove of nature in the city !

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of the most popular hikes in Singapore, around a two hour hike all the way round. Gets very busy on the weekends.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: An amazing place to get close to nature. beautiful reservoirs (water, lake), then the forests and lots of animals for your kids' curioius discovery (monkey, duck, gooses, komondo, etc.)

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: A really scenic view and the trees create a nice ambience to it. You can actually walk from here all the way to Treetop Walk if you have the strength to do so. There are no monkeys and you can walk along the reservoir. The last time I went there, there was no sightings of any monkeys so it generally should be safe. I recommend not to walk along the trail after a rainfall as there are paths where there is no wooden planks and it is just the soil, and so it would be muddy and slippery, so it is best to go on a sunny weather which haven’t rained in a day, at the very least. You can go for a hiking trip there with your friends or your family members.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
This the place that make me feel like not look like Singapore! All Nature and Green! Nice hiking trail and good for Trail Running too!
1 round of trail is about 10km. 😎

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Nice cozy reservoir with natural park. Spent ~2 hours walking with kids. Lots of monkeys along the road which trying to snatch some foods from visitors backpack.
Do bring along plenty of water.
Parking is convenient at the park.
You could actually do cycling there plus
Kayaking too.
Best to go morning or late afternoon.
Crowded but plenty of space for strolling around.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Use to come here every now and then, just to unwind and immerse in nature. The hike usually takes up about 1-1.5 hour, 3 hrs if going up to treetop

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Beautiful sunsets in the evening with the expansive and reflective water contributing to the magical experience  … being there… washes away the worries on my mind and inspires me.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Quite crowded but overall is a very nice chill trekking. One of the most natural trail you can find in Singapore

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
My husband and I took the prunus-petai walk and it became one of the highlights of our Singapore trip. The first half of the track follows along the reservoir with beautiful views of the water. We didn’t see any animals except fish and skinks for this part, but the path is a lovely easy to walk boardwalk.

The second half of the track was a dirt path back to where we started which was a little muddy in spots but still an easy walk. This was where things got exciting because as we entered this part of the walk we saw monkeys! A little way up the track there was a small group of long-tailed macaques that were happy to let us watch them from a very good distance away. As we continued down the track we also saw squirrels and a beautiful hummingbird.

Overall it was an easy walk (1hr 45mins with us dawdling in the heat) that was easy to get to and from by bus, that turned into a great chance to spot wildlife!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Great day hiking with friends, at one of the most standard yet fulfilling places. Macritchie has become such an iconic place for all generations, from our grandparents to our parents and finally us down to our own kids.

Lots to see, lots to discover. Covered about 12 kilometres in a few hours, took it slow as we were all beginners. More places to explore, but certainly not disappointed with this trip! ^^

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
MacRitchie Reservoir is a fantastic playround for nature lovers 🌿 🥰 families, sports enthusiasts, etc - there's something here for everyone !

We took a 3-hour walk/hike from the main reservoir to Winsor Nature Park.

Along the way, we spotted monkeys🙈 squirrels 🐿️, monitor lizards🦎, HUGE ants🐜, birds 🦜... There were people fishing 🎣 kayaking 🚣, running 🏃, having a picnic ...and so much more.

We spent the whole morning there, enjoying the beauty of the reservoir - we were lucky that it was a cool morning.🌅

We had a fantastic time bonding 😍 we didn't even realise that we had walked over 10km.🥳 Thankfully there were shelters for rest along the way.

Still amazes us that this little red dot 🇸🇬 has more to offer than what we can possibly imagine 🎉

⚠️ Stick to the main pathways, wear proper walking/hiking/running shoes. It may get muddy after a heavy downfall.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Good for hiking with several different routes to choose from based on length and difficulty. Treetop walk was closed at the time of visit but managed to go up the Jelutung Tower  for a view  above the trees. Saw lots of monkeys. They travel in groups and are ready to get their hands on your food if you carry them loosely. Best to not bring any. Saw a couple of young wild boars near the Venus trail.
If you look around, you could see more animals in the ecosystem like monitor lizards, squirrels, snakes...
I am a hijabi so not aware of issues with mosquitoes and son did not complain. Some people put on sunhats to protect them. If you don't like walking on earthen ground, you can pick boardwalks which is around the perimeters of the lake. Longest loop is about 11km without Treetop walk.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: 12 Sep 2022: Route 2 hiking trail, cloudy day and pretty cool too. A great day to enjoy the beautiful scenic route...sighted a couple of playful squirrels, stingrays, monitor lizards and common sun skinks along the way.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Good place for hikers and couples to come for a walk and exercise.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Nice view with fresh air! Good for hiking and relaxing!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Beautiful place, if you look carefully especially when on Lornie trail (the boardwalk!), you can see all sorts of amazing stuff - oriental whip snake, monitor lizards (i think?), spiders, mystery insects, stingray looking things, even pitcher plants! Ps: don’t eat or drink anything apart from water when you’re there, the monkeys there can get quite aggressive if they think you have food on you.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of my favorite reservoir parks in Singapore. You could come here for a long walk, a run or take a hike and end up near Bukit Timah reserve.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Plenty of wildlife. I saw wild boar, chickens, monkeys and otters. Pretty awesome.. 👍

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Such an awesome place to go for a walk or run or even just sit and watch the boats racing each other. Conveniently located and well connected with public transport. For people interested to explore further, one can enter through MacRitchie and exit from Bukit Timah nature reserve. Lots of beautiful places to take photos. Must visit for a fun day out.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Great view for a weekend run. Had a good sesh of 12km loop. The track can be a little muddy if it was rainy the night before you visit, but overall not too bad and safe to run.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: A beautiful place to walk amongst nature! Gets very busy at the weekend, midweek is much more peaceful!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
It’s a great escape and don’t be put off by the fact it’s a reservoir, it’s probably the nicest reservoir you’ll get to visit!
A popular activity that can be enjoyed by people of all ages is hiking on the boardwalk by the river as it is a mind calming activity that truly allows one to experience the thick forest and invigorating waters of the reservoir at the same time. And, if you are lucky, you would be able to spot a stingray or even different reptiles taking a dip in the waters.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Absolutely surreal! My favorite trek in all of Singapore! But limited exit options, so be prepared to walk a lot! Really really really beautiful though!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Amazing nature reservoir
11km trail, tree top is must do
Watch out for monitor lizards :)

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Great hike and walk. Nice views

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Love the vibes there, spend an hour plus in Petai boardwalk, can spot some monkeys if you are lucky enough!!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Beautiful beautiful view. I used to come here when I was little and coming back here again with my cousin, it’s spectacular. The vibes are unreal with nature vibes and just makes me feel like I’m in a wonderful Forrest. There’s so many different and unique insects even birds I’ve never seen before.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Good place for a walk, but can be quite challenging!! Will need around 2-3 hours to walk the loop, depending on fitness level!
Went on a Sunday at 3:30pm, and there wasn’t much of a crowd… I did the walk via close-wise direction, and I didn’t lose my way. 😅

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
One of our oldest reservoirs in the central catchment area. The place still retains the olden days vibe.

Slippery when wet!!
This was taken before the rains came. Broadwalk was ok but the inner Lornie Trail was very slippery after the earlier storms. Be very careful going down hill, your normal track shoes won’t have much grip!

Pleasant walk to the start of trails, runners, the lone rooster and also a lone monkey.

The recent rain will do the water level good. From some pictures below you can see the water level dropping.

We spotted an egret and monitor lizard, each minding their own business 😂. Watch the video to see if they interacted!

Carpark is sufficient but it is getting worn out. Time for a repaint and waterproofing. The surroundings are spick and span. A good time to stop and smell the roses before the new year hectic rush dawns upon us. ✌🏻

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
There's different trails for you to explore. Can't remember which trail we chose, but we spent around 2hrs walking and enjoying the view, breathing in fresh air.

There's also a Mr Lim Bo Seng memorial tomb located on top of a hill at Macritchie reservoir.

Really fascinating to see old folks playing the er hu, practicing tai chi and young children playing, all together here at the reservoir.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: An escape from the city life! Most of the trial now has manmade walk way so it's easier to hike up the area! The tree top walk is closed for maintenance until 2021, hoping to see it soon. Was raining when we went but because the tree kind of acts as a shelter so it wasn't bad to the extent of being drenched! But of course we need to beware of any falling trees due to bad weather. Overall was a fun trial, okay to hike in the afternoon too since it's mostly shaded.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: So beautiful and tranquil park. So many trails to choose from. Expect to spot some monkeys on the way. There were canoe renting place near the parking lot too. Will come again to try different trails.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Top choice for hiking and jogging. Link to bukit timah nature reserve. Thick canopy means shaded partially from the sun even on a hot day (:

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
There is so much tranquility to enjoy from a visit to MacRitchie Reservoir. When in the midst of nature, the mind finds calmness as the stress of city living and concerns from Covid-19 are pushed away, even if for a short time. During this period, there are few visitors and this makes the visit more pensive.

As we visited in the late afternoon into twilight hours, we were able to enjoy the day's transformation into night. The already few visitors thinned out as it grew dark. As we were in the park and not along the trails, the lighting led us out of the park. At no time did we feel concerned for our safety, for as long as we did not venture into remote areas and trekking trails.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Beautiful and fun to explore the trails and nature. Lots of wild monkeys around so be careful of them. Use good comfy shoes and bring a bottle of water.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: This is my favorite park to walk in, a full circle will be about 10km. You'll walk alongside the water, past the golf course, in the forest, and if you add the Treetop Walk its a beautiful view and a good addition to your exercise (lots of elevation). You'll see monitor lizards, monkeys, turtles, birds, fish and not too many people :) This is a must go in Singapore

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Clear water, amazing backdrop of clouds, so many different life forms including humans, and a step closer to nature in the pro-nature concrete amalgamation of this beautiful island-country. Apart from this, the reservoir has a rich and interesting history of existence and necessity. Now there are trails, kayaking and picnic spots to entertain the masses.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of the largest and nicest reservoir in Singapore. Came here around morning to breathe in some oxygen. Disconnects you from the electronic world and connect you with nature. You can try kayak as well.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: First of all, Free! Beautiful scenery and lovely views. There is a platoon of monkeys here. They look hungry. Some elder ones will grab your snacks if you are not careful. But normally they are harmless and curious.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
This is the best trail for walkers like me. Place is huge and you would experience dirt road walking. When I got there it starts raining and it smells very fresh and nice after rain.

Seen comodo dragon in the lake. Totally shocked but one local friend told me it is common in there. So keep your eyes open for them.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: I frequently visit MacRitchie reservoir with my family. We enjoy strolling on a boardwalk trail and making a round turn back on gravel rock ground. It's not suitable for people on wheelchairs or strollers as there are a few flight of stairs along the trail. The trail is rather shady with plenty of benches  available for people to rest. You can spot plenty of wildlife like dragonflies, tortoise, arowanas, otters, monkeys monitor lizards, birds etc in this park. The water is very clear and clean, suitable for people who wish to rent a kayak to paddle around the reservoir. There are some designated areas for fishing and apart from that, illegal fishing will attract a fine of sgd3000. Feeding of wildlife is prohibited as well. Be ware of eating in this park as the hungry monkeys are always ready to attack people for food. Water points and toilets are available at the cafe area but not in the main forested area.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Borntoeat.co.id x Borntotravel.co.id
IG: Billy_Christianto

This is one of the best trekking field in Singapore! you guys have to try trekking this are which is located in the middle area of Singapore rather than do shopping in the malls which is mainstream.

I started my trekking from "Venus Dr", but don't follow the main google maps since it's taking you to the different street if you search "Tree Top Walk" direction from "Venus Dr". You guys only need to go the parking area near Venus Dr and there is a proper trek to go to the hill.

The most interesting part in this trekking area is you can meet so many animals directly without any guardian to protect you. The animals could be lizard, snake, squirrel, chicken, fish, worms, giant red ants,etc. But as long as you go forward and not disrupting them, they are just fine.

The trekking to the Tree Top takes like 45 - 60 minutes with around 5-6.5 km depends on the road you take. However, going to the Tree Top is only one way direction which means you need to go out in different way from your entrance, besides you are willing to take extra miles to go back to the entrance which is like 7-8 km from the Treetop Point.

I chose the exit in different way which only takes 5.5km and there is a tower named "Jelutong Tower" in the way you go to the exit area. In the tower, you literally could see the trekking area and the Macritchie Reservoir including the Singapore city. This is one of the best view but beware if it's raining, you'd better not to climb to this tower.

After that, you will see directly in your eyes the Macritchie Reservoir which is very clean park, clean water, fresh air, and it just feels so good. One of the best view in my life, but you'd better to go here in the morning or in the evening like around 2-3 pm.

Overall, I went exit through Lornie Rd and I took the buss there to go to my apartment.

I really recommend for you guys, especially the travelers to do trekking in this area, this is so beautiful!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Wonderful place to recharge and get back to nature in the midst of Singapore's otherwise concrete jungle! There are many walking trails and even a treetop walk. Keep your eyes peeled for long tailed macaque monkeys and monitor lizards. A must visit for any nature or hiking enthusiast.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: This is a great park for hiking with friends and family. The trails are scenic

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: The loveliest nature trail in Singapore. The boardwalk trails are equally lovely. Look carefully and you may be able to spot monkeys, monitor lizards and other animals. If you feel up to it, you can even rent a kayak here.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Singapore’s best trail yet, with lots of side walks and sights which makes you feel as though you are overseas!

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Looking forward for the treetop to open. Nice trail and a relaxing view. It will bring you closer to the nature.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: The oldest manmade reservoir in Singapore. During Covid-19 period, F&B that is situated near main carpark is closed. Vending machines and public toilets are available at central pavilion and the Singapore Canoe Federation (SCF) kiosk nearby. The time to complete one whole round of reservoir by walking is approximately 4-5 hours, shorter if you are running.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of the best natural place in Singapore where you can plan for tracking and running. There's one of the best place to see natural tree view from top tree walk.if you are.planning to visit spare at least 3-4 hours...

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: This reservoir is a favorite of many in Singapore. Offers a great hiking trail, beautiful scenes of nature all throughout... plenty of photo opportunity... so put on your hiking boots, grab a BIG bottle of water and set out on a “green” adventure.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Excellent place for trekking and jogging. It has many trials. Tree top trial was superb. Nice place to have a refreshing time with mother nature.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: MacRitchie Reservoir Park is definitely a great place for a walk, a trek and a good run no matter when you're alone to have a good quiet time to yourself while enjoying the sounds, sights and smells of nature or with your friends or family for an enjoyable and great outing together. The trails are long and there are some obstacles along the way but overall it is manageable but remember to bring water along since there are water coolers at big stops only. There is wild life to look out for such as Monitor Lizards, some wet land reserve birds and chickens to name a few. It is also possible to walk from here to Bukit Timah Reserve which is about 10km distance, taking about half a day to complete.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Picturesque sunset views right here in Singapore.  Best time for taking stunning sunset photos: 6:30pm-7:15pm.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: From a tourist point of view this was a lovely break from the crowds. We thoroughly enjoyed the trials and saw so much wildlife. Would definitely recommend to others.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
A good hiking place all throughout the day except in the evening as the area has no lights and scary. That was unexpected that we will still be there very late.

It's okay to walk even if the sun is bright as the trail path is covered with trees. You can hear alot of natural sounds like chirping of the birds,  the monkies, frogs and some more animals.

Once you reach the ranger station there's a toilet and water refilling station so no need to cary too much water. Mc Ritchie is a good hiking and distressing place. I really really love the place.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
One of the best places in Singapore to do a good trail run of approximately 10.5km. Recommend to start at reservoir car park and do a clockwise if you are running.

If you are breeze walking, walk anti clockwise.
Check out the tree top walk whilst you are here.

Full of nature -
Montor lizards and monkeys.

Best to avoid early mornings as it is hard to find a carpark and place is packed with people.

Perfectly fine to go on off peak hike before 7am.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
MacRitchie Resevoir is a great place to escape urban Singapore. There are areas along the trails and boardwalks in the park which have you surrounded by nature. If you take the waterside boardwalks and invlude the treewalk, the full walk around the resevoir can stretch over 8 miles. I see monitor lizards, longtail macaque monkeys, and turtles every walk here. A refreshing walk into the woods of Singapore. Enjoy the breeze, and admire the various trees & shrubs; flowers & leaves as you pass by.
Put on walking shoes, mosquito stickers, hat, caps, sunglasses & use umbrella if necessary.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Awesome Broadway walk with greeneries. A great hiking place for nature lovers. Great views and peaceful a great way to connect with nature. Many trees, flora, animal and insects to explore as well. Fresh air, monkey, monitor lizards, birds are just a few to mention.
Weekends can get crowded, weekday mornings gives you the best time to enjoy the calm & tranquility of the place. A must visit for all to see a different side of Singapore concrete jungle.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: My family completed route 4  (yellow) today. A great accomplishment for my family. Due to raining, some parts are quite muddy. Not easy to walk.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Mac Ritchie is quite luscious in nature and there is a lot of greenery around that area. It is like an escape from the city. It is extremely calm and peaceful. There is also a lot of monkeys so you might feel like you are bonding with the wild life.
The water is vey clear and there is a lot of scenic beauty.
I also appreciate that there is a washing area for shoes. It is extremely thoughtful of them.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: It was beautiful, even though it rained part of my hike. I was able to see monkeys, a squirrel and a rooster. Keep in mind most animals do not want to be seen so I. Sure more we're lurking. The monkeys did not attempt to snatch anything from me, but I followed the rules and did not bring food.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
This is an urban eco-oasis that's easy to access via the bus. The trail is 90% covered by a natural canopy,  so expect to stay cooler while hiking at a moderate pace or trail running. Good running or trail shoes are recommended. The trail has lot's of people on it, but does not feel crowded at all! Don't worry about mosquitoes or bugs - I personally didn't encounter any. The boardwalk trail along the resovoir shoreline is narrow and more suited for leisurely walking than jogging.

The signs are very well demarcated. Should an emergency arise while on the trail, there are frequent passer-bys who would be willing to help.

Bring along lots of water on this trail. Depending on where you start the trail from, you might be walking for a while before encountering toilet facilities, water fountain, or canteen/kiosk. The trailhead closest to Upper Thompson Rd is the best place to begin your trek, either towards the Treetop Walk, or around the lake.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
I went here as a break from the hustle and bustle of the city and I got that. There were a number of walks signposted of different lengths and degrees of difficulty. I opted for the boardwalk round the reservoir and it was a delight. The occasional walker and jogger, but if i saw a dozen folk in 3 hours I'd be exaggerating. I'd recommend stocking up on water from the reasonably priced cafe at the beginning. The walk has benches at regular intervals and information signs. I did wonder if the placing of the snake information sign at abut halfway was deliberate. Talk about rock and a hard place! Still, our paths never crossed, but I did see an impressive array of bird and dragonfly life.
I didn't make it to the TreeTop Walk, so one for next time. If you want to unwind, or maybe use the exercise equipment, I can heartily recommend a visit here.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Excellent park with wilderness areas and many walking paths. Troops of long tailed macaques, monitor lizards, shiny skinks and other wildlife to look for. The price is right too.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Started the hike at Windsor Nature Park and it was lovely because there weren’t many people. But once we got to Macritchie, there were tons more people. Saw a couple of wild and small monkeys along the way. People were quite orderly when hiking along the pathway.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Trekked the yellow route (11km) in 3 hours, with medium pace. The tree top walk is still under renovation so didn’t get to experience that. It was a great workout and we were able to spot a few wildlife! :))

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Downside - hard to get to on public transport so cabbing/ driving there is prob your best bet. Brightside, spend a day in nature on a nice hike and spot the wildlife. We spent about 3 Hours walking about and saw monkeys, monitor lizards and more.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Might get a bit difficult to reach using public transport depending on where you live. But, please put in the effort or take a cab to get here. I promise you won’t be disappointed. This place grows on you. You can spend half a day or a bit more walking around and enjoying moments that would transport you into a rain forest kind of an environment - all of this in the middle of the city. There are some water activities like kayaking that you can do. You can check out a new route for trekking each time you visit. You must try the treetop walk as well as it’s gorgeous. Overall, wish there were some food stalls here and there to find relief but absolutely love this place even without them.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
If walking/light trekking is one of your plus point or something you love to do.. then this is d place to go.

You will be welcomed by nature's flora n fauna that are available here. To be part of Singapore's natural forest in the City, this place is worth every penny. Not just bekoz its free to enter, it offers more than just what you deserve.

Butterflies, Monkeys, Durians, hidden streams and more.. this is a great place to go if you have hours to spare. We kid you not about getting more than what you deserve.

Just a precaution, as with other parks, pls be careful and observe rules set. This is to ensure we maintain d place for future generations to come.

Cheers!

#macritchie #macritchiereservoir #singapore #nature #natureinacity #minutesawayfromcity #forest

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Best kept secret  of Singapore!!!MacRitchie Reservoir spells out calmness and its serenity captivates me more each time I go there. Every morning I find refuge from the strife of urban life in the jungle right amidst the city- Singapore.
Walking trails along the water’s edge make my daily morning walk a memorable feat each day. It is truly a reservoir that one loves to reminisce about. Traversing the trail of MacRitchie Reservoir makes it the most momentous escape for everyone in Singapore who ventures out in this refreshing urban jungle

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: MacRitchie Reservoir will have you experience a completely different perspective of Singapore. Away from the crowded metropolitan life, located in the centre of this island, is the MacRitchie Reservoir. A place so peaceful and serene that you would wish to stay there. It’s an amazing place for nature lovers and trekkers. The Treetop Walk is the highlight. Kayak along with safety precautions is available too. Not only will you experience nature at its best but also learn about different types of trees and species of insects. It’s a different world altogether. I love it.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
MacRitchie Reservoir is part of a network of reservoirs located in the central part of Singapore.

more than just being a reservoir, MacRitchie is also a nature park, with kilometers of trails to hike through, and with the recent inclusion of the Park Connector network, and also linkage of trails with other nature reserves' trails, MacRitchie is the best starting point to start a hike, or end it. It's also a perfect place for trail running, or having a water-side picnic with the family.

Connected parks/reserves include Bukit Timah Hill, Dairy Farm Nature Park and Hindhede Nature Park, all located within the Bukit Timah Nature Reserve

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Great place to exercise and trek in Singapore which covers great distance with various choices of taking the plank walks or the nature paths.

It has a few stops for toilets and noted one point where you can refill water.

The trek on nature paths are shady because of the trees. During the rain, the trees also provide significant shades. But noted a few signs to warn people to beware of falling branches during bad weather.

Been here multiple times and always bumped into the monkeys, monitor lizards, snakes, terapines, fish, butterflies, dragonflies etc.

This place is not recommended for people who are bringing stroller because when it rains, the nature paths are muddy and the width of the wooden planks on the plank walks are quite narrow.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
See this little cute rascal hopping around, glancing at whoever as if recognizing friends.
And the monkey's expression is as if we are the intruders of his territory.

The running tracks at MacRitchie Reservoir bring back memories of school cross country events held here decades ago.
How an absolutely untrained class rep runner had to be pacesetter, didn’t know the running pace and breathing method, but only kept running whenever hearing footsteps behind. Finally collapsed at finishing line. Woke up seeing a trophy. Not a dark horse but an inexperienced pony who shocked all by
singlemindedness & determination.

MacRitchie, memories to revisit, a place to be refreshed & recharged.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Review for 'MacRitchie Nature Trail' (Feb 2022). We visited this place with the intention of seeing the 'Tree-Top Walk'
1) Maps are inadequately placed and do not cover this trail accurately. The signage are poor, lacks detail and is misleading. There were occasions were we ended up taking the wrong turn
3) As the name suggests ‘rest-huts’ on this trail are just huts. There is no facility for seating more than 3, or drinking water and no rest-rooms
4) Only one rest-room on this trail is at Ranger Station. One has to walk minimum 5 kms just to get there
5) Ranger Station near Tree-Top had no personnel or staff manning it. There is no place for seating as well unless you are prepared to squat on the floor
6) This part of the trail is just not meant for elderly. No facilities at all for them
7) No first-aid kits either along this trail. You are simply on your own if you trip or fall
8) Exits are not clear. Exit road close to Ranger Station is marked as private property and cordoned off. Also exits like Venus Loop for instance nearly doubled our walking to the nearest car park. The signage didn’t indicate this
9) Venus Car-Park doesn't even have signage for Taxi/Grab drop-off or pick-up

If you are a casual walker, please avoid this trail. Infact, there should be a warning indicating the inherent risk of taking this trail.

Its an amazing trail for adventure seeking people who love nature. The best part is Tree Top Walk.
You should start early by 7:30 am so that you can be at Tree top by 8:30 am (opening time) and enjoy the morning freshness or else it gets hot during day time and you can't enjoy the trek that much.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
It's a rain water reservoir, it's a nice walk for the weekend.
I'd avoid walking around noon since it gets pretty hot, also bring water since the next rest stop is an hour or so away.
After checking the reservoir you can walk to the tree top walk.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
A very lovely park, but do go during the week days as it is the most popular park for runners and hikers during the weekend. When the sky is clear, and the sun is up, you get to see the sun’s rays radiating through the top of the canopy down onto the ground of the forested woods.
It is very tranquil to take the Petai trail which skirts the shore of the Reservoir. Admire and enjoy the peace and solidarity during the weekdays.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Good trail walk but gets very crowded during weekends/PH.

review_text: Facility not to world standard. The broad walk to narrow and no toilet. No user friendly for elderly and disable. Need children play ground for family outing.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: The walk around the lake is absolutely amazing. Go there, rent a kayak, walk in the rain forests, rest and relax by the lake, peaceful nature walk. Best time to go - around 4pm so that you are not hit by the hot afternoon sun.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
I absolutely am thrilled to trek here. Though the scenery isn't the best, the path and nature is amazing.

Some tips:
1) Try not to go after rainy day as there will be slippery mud along the way, unless you're okay with getting your shoes muddy & there's chances of falling down.
2) Monkeys are generally not aggressive there, but please do not provoke them or feed them.
3) Bring along your water bottle as there's only 1 pitstop for refilling your water & going to the washroom.
4) If you're afraid of insects, you might want to bring along an insect repellent as well.

There are also other animals to be seen there such as Wild Boar; Monitor Lizard; Rooster; Snake etc
Park is open from 7am-7pm.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: nice

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: So, this is one of the nature reserves in Singapore. Perfect for trail running. The walk to the treetop walk is a bit inclined and long so please be careful if you have any knew problems.  You will find a lot of families hiking around the park on weekends.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: A great place for a walk or trail running. There are a number of different paths. You could park at Venus Drive and take the Board Walk to MacRitchie Reservoir. This morning, we started from Mushroom Cafe, and took the trail towards Jerantung Tower, Jering and skirted along the shore of the reservoir via Golf Link before reaching back at Mushroom Cafe. It is nice to pack food, and find a nice spot to enjoy a little picnic. Nearest MRT : Caldecott/ Marymount MRT. Bus: 980, 167, 74, 52, 852

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Towards the end, the park became busy with many athletes in training as well as casual walkers/runners.Later I was told this was the only forest in Singapore. I really enjoyed running through the woods.  Honest confession, I had difficulty breathing with high humidity and hot temperature, I had to monitor my heart rate throughout.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: The tranquility of this place gives you a nice quiet feeling, a sense of calmness and very near to nature if you visit on weekdays. But on weekends, it turns into a world full of foreign natives. You can meet all the people of the world in their best behaviour.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: A beautiful place which is inhabitated by hundreds of species of animals and plants. Recommended to students and tourists and all ages of the public to come and learn about the exotic species within this reservoir. This reservoir also encourages people to take part in the kayaking activity in its clean waters. A splendid place for a peaceful day out jogging, walking, cycling, skateboarding, scooter-riding and more.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:

Good place to breath in some fresh air, fresh up your mind and prepare yourself to enter another working week with new challenges.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir

Very nice lake there have money so must be careful.  Better not bring plastic bag et. Money very smart wann try to grab your food.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: The top  destination for trekking livers. Better be mindful of the park's maps and your energy level so as to not overcommit. The reservoir offers shorter paths. Bring food and drinks but beware monkeys will harass you to get your stash so be discreet and conceal them. A grocery bag carried in plain site is strong trigger for them haha

review_text: Good place for a bit of jungle trekking but would not recommend going during the monsoon season/when it's just rained as some parts were very muddy and slippery. The Tree Top Walk was still closed as well.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
A great trail that's off the tourist trail. Take the MRT to Caldecott and it's a short walk away (no bus or taxi required).

The blue route to the tree top walkway is listed as 'moderate /difficult' and is about 10km, but certainly worth the walk. Picking up the boardwalk on the way back adds a gentle finish to the walk, but does add another 2km.
Spotted during a rainy walk : Wild boar, Drongo, Snake (Green 12" long), Monkeys, Terrapin and Cloud monitor water lizard. (Not a wildlife expert, so best description).

A good day out away from the crowd downtown.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of the best hiking trails in Singapore. Anyone who ever visits Singapore must explore this Gem. However the bridge is closed till June for renovation but its an awesome getaway from the City life and the glass buildings. The Forest is well kept and track well made..

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Very nice place to visit

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: My best time in Singapore, best place to relax, good walking experience in all season, specially in rain

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: I can't believe they call it a park. It was a huge area if you want to enjoy nature, the forest inside the city. When I first saw it, I knew I would love it very much. It was calm and fresh. You could learn a lot about nature, different kinds of trees, wild animals and see money hang around there. The tree top walk was amazing. It was the long bridge, from there you could see the whole area and the lake from far away. The view from there was magnificent. If you like hiking, it's your place for sure. I think I took long hard route because it took me about 4 hours to walk all the way around. The area beside Golf link with the lake was really calm, when I was there, many people were hanging around and it was fun. Walking in the forest was another amazing experience, too. All the way up and down, follow small paths.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: One of the best hikes in Singapore it does not have tons of routes but it is always very nice.

review_text: One of the best places for a morning trail in Singapore. You won't feel that you are in the middle of a bustling city when you are here. Multiple trails to chose from, with varying distances. If you are in the mood, try getting to Bukit Timah / Dairy farm for a great morning workout

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
If you are here at the main entrance and intend to make your way to the tree top trail, bear in mind the bridge at the tree top trail is ONE WAY only. That means NO turning back.

After you make your 5km+ to the tree top trail, and should you decide to walk over the bridge, be advised that there's another 6km back to the car park at main entrance.

Fishing spot here is as good as none, quite impossible to cast your reel at the tiny authorised fishing spot.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
Victims of Circumstances

Before my retirement, I find life is meaningless and my career is in a rut. What would you do if you were me? Most people would accept the inevitable rather than take the challenge to find a solution to life problem. They believe that they are victims of circumstances. Do you?

Instead of feeling despair, I decide to take the road less travelled rather than follow the flock to embark on an inner spiritual journey of heroic quest to find out what my life destiny is in this existence.  In this unconventional approach, I seek the help of a deck of metaphysical cards aka my spiritual guide, the support from the friendly Universe, and protection from the light beings from the mineral kingdom.

Within three months of the journey, I successfully find out that my life destiny is in writing with the help of my spiritual guide. Taking the cue from my spiritual guide that my life destiny is in writing, I take the plunge to write my memoir regarding my heroic quest over a period of fourteen years. Finally, I successfully fulfill my life destiny in writing with the publication of a piece of work on heroic quest.

What I wish to demonstrate is that we are not victims of circumstances. We are the products of our choices only when we are determined to find out what our life destiny is in this existence regardless of age, education, circumstances etc. as I have revealed in my book, Going Home, how I find my life destiny at the age of 55 and get my work published at 72. Moreover, I am just an ordinary man on the street with an “O” level without any writing experience nor ever attended a writing course before.

You can skip the time and head to Tree Top Walk starting from Venus Car Park, Take bus 162M in Blk 454 bus station, from Orchard Street.
Bring sufficient water if you don't have you can drink cold water at Radio station on the way to Tree Top Walk Gate.

review_text:
A very nice and beautiful place.Lots of serenity around.Takes some time to visit the specific structures around the area. It is a favourite place for many people, be it joggers, hikers, strollers, families with children , etc. There is a western cafe/ restaurant , aslo a public car park.
Dated : 05/11/2017 ( Sunday ).
Updated : 15/05/2018 ( Tuesday ).
On a slope is the grave of  Mr. Lim Boo Seng our local hero who leads the 136 unit's resistance against the invading Imperial Japanese Army during World War 2.Unfortunatly he was captured and tortured and died as a p.o.w. In the forest there is a ruin site of a formal Shinto Temple built and used by the Japanese Army.It is difficult to locate and get to now as is covered by the thick forest vegetation.
Updated : 17/03/2019 ( Sunday ).
Added 14 photos.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text: Nature park with decent trails to "hike". The main loop is just under 11km. There are lots of boardwalks added, and some parts of the trail are currently undergoing maintenance. Hadn't visited in a long time. It feels like the walk is simpler and less challenging, compared to the past. Forest feels more lush (maybe due to the constant rainy weather), but some of the paths have been reorganised or closed off.

review_text: The trail is not that difficult. It is long though. If you love to walk and explore, this place is for you. Do carry water bottle to stay hydrated and to refill at different points. name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
(Translated by Google) The perfect place to go for a walk around the reservoir in magnificent vegetation. A superb forest and magnificent landscape not to be missed. I came across birds, insects, turtles and even monkeys on the boardwalk. I recommend for all nature lovers. Very good time spent.

(Original)
L'endroit parfait pour aller se balader autour du réservoir dans une magnifique végétation. Une superbe forêt et de magnifique paysage à ne pas louper. J'ai croiser des oiseaux, insectes, tortues et même des singes sur la promenade. Je recommande pour tous les amoureux de la nature. Très bon moment passé.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
(Translated by Google) It is located in the middle of Singapore. After a week or so in Singapore, I wanted to find something more natural than the glamorous city center. I also visited Singapore Botanic Gardens and Night Safari, so I didn't really have any other places to visit. This is the place I finally came to after looking around. Not so famous in Singapore, even a Grab driver asked, "What's with the MacRitchie Reservoir that you're visiting?" When we arrived at the entrance to the park, it seemed that there were cafes and restaurants of its own, but the hygiene conditions were not good. There was also a drainage system nearby, and since it was a reservoir at first, I thought it might be a landscape far from the natural scenery. But after only a few minutes of walking along the trail, I changed my mind. Unexpectedly, the scenery of the dense forest and the reservoir was superb. The promenade was well maintained and there were many people exercising. I couldn't finish the trail due to time constraints, but it was a place I would like to enjoy slowly and a little longer when visiting later.

(Original)

Singapore Botanic Gardens도 방문했고, Night Safari도 방문했던 터라 추가적으로 방문할 곳이 마땅치 않았다. 결국 이것저것 뒤져보다가 방문하게 된 장소이다. 싱가포르 내에서도 그리 유명하지 않은지 Grab 기사도 "MacRitchie Reservoir에는 어떤게 있어서 방문하는 거니?"하고 물어보기까지 했다. 공원 입구에 도착하자 나름대로 카페랑 식당도 있는 듯 했으나 위생상태가 좋아 보이지 않았다. 근처에 배수 시설도 있었고, 애초에 저수지 인지라 자연경관과는 거리가 먼 풍경이 아닌가 생각했다. 하지만 Trail을 따라 몇 분 정도만 걷자 생각이 바뀌었다. 예상 외로 울창한 숲과 저수지가 어우러진 풍경이 일품이었다. 산책로도 잘 가꾸어져 있어 운동하는 사람들도 많았다. 시간 관계상 트레일을 끝내지 못했지만 추후 방문 시 천천히, 그리고 조금 더 길게 즐기고 싶은 그런 장소였다.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Great park with lots of wild animals. Admission is free.

Most of the paths are not wheelchair accessible. However, two people can manage the stairs along the path along the reservoir with a stroller.

Die Wege sind größtenteils nicht rollstuhlgerecht. Zu zweit kann man die Treppen auf dem Weg am Stausee entlang mit einem Kinderwagen aber bewältigen.
Wir hatten einen tollen Ausflug, der unseren Urlaub noch schöner gemacht hat.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
(Translated by Google) THE GREEN PERFECT IN THE MIDDLE OF SINGAPORE

In the last days of August, Singapore "frustrated" when it started to "turn over" to enter autumn. The fresh air mixed with the scent of plants everywhere easily makes people fall in love and feel more excited for the discovery. Singapore at this time often has sudden rains.

MacRitchie Reservoir is a true tropical park with straight lines of old trees and luxuriant flora that welcomes visitors. For those who visit Singapore for the first time, they must be quite impressed with the freshness and clean green environment of this country, so when coming to MacRitchie, everything seems to be more pure, especially after the rains.

Arriving at MacRitchie Reservoir, you will understand why this place is known as the green gem in the heart of Singapore. Because it seems to be separate and in this place we do not see the hustle and bustle of life, only the sound of birds singing, the sound of flowers singing with the wind and clouds. Sometimes there are some giant creatures peeking out from behind the trees, making you suddenly feel that nature is so lovely and close.

You will feel the fresh and airy space in harmony with the charming natural green color of the high-class golf course. The green lawns along the lake will also be an ideal place to rest or take pictures. Opposite is a beautiful natural freshwater lake like in the fresco that makes many people flutter.

To get to MacRitchie Reservoir by public transport, you can either catch a bus to the 'MacRitchie Reservoir' stop on Lornie Road, or take the Circle Line to Caldecott MRT and walk 10 minutes from there. There are multiple entrances to the park, but this is the main entrance and the closest entrance to the park's attractions.

(Original)
VIÊN NGỌC XANH GIỮA LÒNG SINGAPORE

Những ngày cuối tháng 8, Singapore “đỏng đảnh” khi bắt đầu “trở mình” để vào thu. Không khí trong lành hoà quyện cùng hương cỏ cây ở khắp mọi nơi dễ khiến người ta say đắm và cảm thấy phấn khích khích hơn cho công cuộc khám phá. Singapore thời điểm này thường có những cơn mưa bất chợt.

MacRitchie Reservoir là một công viên nhiệt đới đúng chất với những hàng cây già thẳng tắp và hệ thực vật xum xuê bao quanh chào đón du khách. Với những ai du lịch Singapore lần đầu chắc hẳn khá ấn tượng với sự trong lành và môi trường xanh sạch của đất nước này, vì vậy khi đến với MacRitchie dường như mọi thứ còn tinh khiết hơn, đặc biệt là sau những trận mưa.

Đặt chân đến MacRitchie Reservoir, bạn sẽ lý giải được tại sao nơi này lại được mệnh danh là viên ngọc xanh giữa lòng Singapore. Bởi lẽ dường như nó tách bạch và tại nơi này chúng ta không thấy những bộn bề cuộc sống những âm thanh xô bồ, chỉ có tiếng chim hót, tiếng hoa lá reo ca với gió mây. Thỉnh thoảng là vài sinh vật khổng lồ lấp ló sau những tàng cây khiến bạn chợt thấy thiên nhiên thật đáng yêu và gần gũi.

Bạn sẽ cảm nhận được không gian thoáng đãng trong lành hòa với màu xanh tự nhiên quyến rũ là khu sân golf cao cấp. Những thảm cỏ xanh mướt dọc men hồ cũng sẽ là địa điểm dừng chân thật lý tưởng để nghỉ ngơi hoặc tranh thủ chụp ảnh. Đối diện là hồ nước ngọt tự nhiên đẹp như trong bức bích họa khiến không ít người phải xao xuyến.

👉🏻Để đến MacRitchie Reservoir bằng phương tiện công cộng, bạn có thể bắt xe buýt đến trạm dừng ‘MacRitchie Reservoir’ trên Đường Lornie, hoặc đi Circle Line đến Caldecott MRT và từ đó đi bộ 10 phút. Có nhiều lối để vào công viên, nhưng đây là lối vào chính và lối vào gần nhất với các điểm tham quan của công viên.

name: MacRitchie Reservoir
review_text:
(Translated by Google) You would almost forget that there is also nature to be found in Singapore. Here you can walk for hours, without having the idea that you are so close to the city. This unique area feels like a rainforest, with its beautiful vegetation. The lake was once specially created to serve as a water reservoir for the city. You can walk all around it on a path of planks. If desired, you can deviate to do the Tree Top Walk, for example. Around the lake is flat, but as soon as you start walking differently, there can be a difference in height, or even stairs. We had a lovely walk here.
Watch out for the 'sweet' monkeys. They are not shy, but can startle and bite if you hold out a selfie stick to them, for example. A loose bag or camera is also not safe. Feeding is not necessary, and therefore prohibited.

(Original)
Je zou bijna vergeten dat er ook nog natuur te vinden is in Singapore. Hier kan je uren wandelen, zonder dat je het idee hebt zo dicht bij de stad te zijn. Dit unieke gebied voelt aan als regenwoud, met zijn prachtige begroeiing. Het meer is ooit speciaal aangelegd om als waterreservoir te dienen voor de stad. Je kan er geheel omheen lopen over een pad van planken. Desgewenst kan je afwijken om bijvoorbeeld de Tree Top Walk te doen. Rond het meer is vlak, maar zodra je anders gaat lopen, kan er hoogte verschil zijn, of zelfs trappen. Wij hebben hier heerlijk gewandeld.
Kijk wel uit voor de 'lieve' aapjes. Ze zijn niet schuw, maar kunnen wel schrikken en toehappen als je bijvoorbeeld een selfiestick naar ze uit steekt. Een losliggend tasje of camera is ook niet veilig. Voeren is niet nodig, en dan ook verboden.
